#. [part]
#: data/campaigns/Two_Brothers/scenarios/1_Rooting_Out_A_Mage.cfg:12
msgid ""
"The remote village of Maghre in the eastern reaches of the kingdom of "
"Wesnoth was once a peaceful village, its villagers mostly unaware of the "
"comings and goings of the wider world. However, a darkness spread from the "
"northlands, shattering the peace and tranquility of the region; a dark mage "
"was the harbinger of this shadow, the spreader of havoc and despair."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: data/campaigns/Two_Brothers/scenarios/1_Rooting_Out_A_Mage.cfg:16
msgid ""
"Skeletons and zombies left cattle and beasts of burden dead in the fields. "
"Barnyards all around of Maghre were set on fire. The Villagers knew that "
"their biggest fears have come true and they felt like all hope was lost"
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: data/campaigns/Two_Brothers/scenarios/1_Rooting_Out_A_Mage.cfg:20
msgid ""
"Many of the villagers looked to Bjarn, the local mage, for leadership in "
"this desperate situation and he promised to send for aid. He armed the "
"strongest villagers with stores from the armory and sent word to his brother "
"Arne, the leader of a mercenary band of horseman."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: data/campaigns/Two_Brothers/scenarios/1_Rooting_Out_A_Mage.cfg:24
msgid ""
"Unsettled by the unexpected plea for help by his brother and uncertain which "
"dangers lied ahead, Arne gathered some of his men and hurried to Maghre to "
"help Bjarn."
msgstr ""

